The paper deals with 3D image registration, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The use of GPUs for parallel processing is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests categories such as multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of variational methods, which are often used in machine learning (cs.LG).
